<chapter><title>User Interface Configuration</title>

<sect1><title>Configuring the Interface</title>
<para>
  The user interface can be custom configured to suit user preferences. This includes the ability to changes the
  colours of the axes, graphs, error bars and grid. The type and colour of the font used to display text on the
  grpahs is also configfurable.
</para>
<sect2><title>Changing UI colours</title>
<para>
  The above is all achieved through the <command>view</command> menu. The colours of the various view elements are 
  changed by simply
  selecting that element from within the view menu. The resulting window allows the colour selection either from
  the supplied pallette, or by adjusting the individual RGB combination. Colours can also be added to a group of
  custom colours, useful for quick selection.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2><title>Font configuration</title>
<para>
  The font type is also changed from the <command>view</command> menu. Any standard true type font can 
  be used. TODO!!!
  Along with type, the colour and size of the graph font are also configurable.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2><title>Show/hide Directions</title>
<para>
  The default is to have all three directions of a data set displayed. This however, is also configurable. This is
  achieved through the <command>view</command> menu, by checking or unchecking the appripriate directions.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2><title>Show/hide error bars </title>
<para>
  The default is to have the error bars enabled. To disble the error bars, simply check the Show error bars item in
  the <command>view</command> menu.
</para
</sect2>

<sect2><title>Show/hide the grid</title>
<para>
  The default is to have the grid enabled. To disble the grid, simply check the Show grid item in
  the <command>view</command> menu.
</para>
</sect2>


</sect1>

